title: For Sale:  Original Tula Mosin M91/30 PE Sniper
postcontent: ***$2500 obo***I WILL SHIP TO ANY STATEPLEASE EMAIL ME FOR MORE PICTURES!!! I HAVE TONS!!! ARMSLIST WILL NOT ALLOW ME TO UPLOAD MORE THAN THREEI ACCEPT PAYMENT VIA USPS MONEY ORDER, CASH (IF FACE TO FACE), AND VENMO!Have for sale a pretty rare rifle. This is an ORIGINAL Mosin sniper rifle. Serial numbers on barrel shank, buttplate, bolt, and magazine plate match (the magazine plate was restamped to match). Technically this is not a PE sniper, it is a Top Mount (versus the later side mount) PEM sniper. What makes this even more rare, is that not only is it "CП" marked indicating it was in fact built to be a sniping rifle, but it is double-dated AND "MO" marked. Very, Very, uncommon. Bore is very good with strong lands and grooves. The bolt was polished at some point. The trigger on this is damn near what you'd expect on a modern-day AR15 or Remington 700. It is VERY crisp and has almost no slack, which is what is typical of original Russian 91/30 snipers. Also, it has the correct higher front sight post (versus the shorter one found on basic issue infantry rifles. The shorter sights which were also typically set to the left, were used to compensate for the fact that standard issue rifles were sighted in with the bayonet fixed. Snipers were not put throught this process because they didnt need it, due to their inherent accuracy). I will also include a Cold-War Era set of whitewash goggles (basically sunglasses for snipers, helped them see in the snow), and leather lens caps.
